as a child what tv product offer did you have to have here's mine early 's i got my parents to send off for this decoder kit you put this plastic sheet over the tv screen and used their marker to trace over parts of letters each week you added to the letter parts until the secret message was revealed i enjoyed the process but i must have been disappointed in the message as this is the first and last thing i ever ordered from tv as a child i delivered papers a lot this was in the early 's so spending money was no problem for me as i have routes and make about cllose to bucks a month that is a lot of money to have for a kid yrs old so i love watching cartoons and then some other sci fi shows but encounter a lot of tv ads at that age i was very much into sports especially volleyball i was on one of the state volleyball junior squads plus because of having training but not hard i was always wanting to look good like the muscle bound maniacs so one day watching tv after i got home from pracitce i watch some tv ad about getting your abs tight and firm in less then weeks thought it was a good idea so i just bought it and asked my dad to pay for it and i paid him back with my newspaper money i was so disappointed when i got the equipment and then it showed you what to do with it after weeks following the instructions nothing much had happened with my workout and it taught me that never buy tv ad things unless you seen it in person first and then tried it and then buy it if the money is worth it because it is all a scam Internet fraud Poker jargon Make money fast About a Boy Advance fee fraud Microeconomics Wheel of Fortune Avenue Q Serial Social rule Atari 8-bit family Volleyball Humphrey Bogart Warren Buffett Surveillance Ayyavazhi mythology The Fairly OddParents Dog training Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Bulk vending David Beckham Advertising Obi-Wan Kenobi EastEnders Garfield Television in the United States Ed, Edd n Eddy Neopets Opus Dei Meat Loaf $ale o